                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>I may, however mention in <add>?</add> to <persName>Mr DeSola</persName><lb/> the\n                lecture was got up at a very short notice<lb/> &amp; being addressed to a mixed\n                audience <del>was</del><lb/> became a difficult subjectâ€”he however<lb/> acquitted\n                himself with his usual ability<lb/> &amp; has acquired some reputation from it.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">It has caused quite a sensation<lb/> among 'the clergy' here &amp;\n                the messenger<lb/> sincerely<add>?</add> has a good deal thought of from<lb/> being\n                the first Eastern who has <add>?</add><lb/> these northern shores.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">I should like <del>you</del> to insert the<lb/> account of the\n                lecture as from a friend<lb/> without putting any signature to the<lb/>\n                communication as my writings are generally<lb/> confined to professional &amp; not\n                religious<lb/> subjects. Yours very sincerely</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(4)\">\n                <persName role=\"author\">A H David</persName>\n            </p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3ff3mk73/canvas/p2"
